---
layout: base
permalink: /index.html
title: 'Explore Apologetics'
description: 'Eleventy starter using modern CSS, fluid type, fluid spacing, flexible layout and progressive enhancement.'
blog:
  title: 'Main Note Box'
  intro: "These are the main notes in this digital zettelkasten. Choose one to get started, or go to the Index page to choose a section to explore."
---

<div class="wrapper">
  <header class="full | section" style="--spot-color: var(--color-primary)">
      {% svg "divider/soft-top", null, "seperator" %}

    <div class="section__inner flow region">
      <h1 class="text-center" style="color: var(--color-light);">{{ title }}</h1>
    </div>

    {% svg "divider/soft-bottom", null, "seperator" %}
  </header>

  <article class="full | region">
    <div class="wrapper flow prose">
      <h2 id="an-eleventy-starter">Welcome</h2>
      <p>
        You've stumbled onto the Apologetics Atlas, a subset of my analog zettelkasten that I'm publishing online to share what I'm learning with others who want to learn about Christian doctrine and apologetics.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>There are 3 ways to explore this site:</strong> Search the: <a href="/noteindex/">Index</a>,
        <a href="/blog/">Main Note Box</a>, or <a href="/bibliography/">Bibliography</a>.
      </p>
      <p><strong>Have fun exploring</strong> and let me know if you find any issues or have ideas for improvements!</p>
    </div>
  </article>

  <section class="full | region">
    <div class="wrapper flow prose">
      <h2>{{ blog.title }}</h2>
      <!-- blog intro text is optional. -->

      {% if blog.intro %}
        <p>{{ blog.intro }}</p>
      {% endif %}

      <div class="feature |  region region-space-l">
        <custom-masonry layout="50-50">
          <!-- loop posts -->
          {% set itemList = collections.allPosts %}
					{% asyncEach item in itemList.slice(0, 4) %}
						{% set definedDate = item.date %}
						{% include "partials/card-blog.njk" %}
					{% endeach %}
        </custom-masonry>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>
